				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="dablink"><span class="plainlinks selfreference">For the Wikipedia editing policy on use of regional variants in Wikipedia, see <a href="Wikipedia_Manual_of_style#National_varieties_of_English" title="Wikipedia:Manual of style" class="mw-redirect">Wikipedia:Manual of style#National varieties of English</a></span></div>
<p>This is one of a series of articles about the differences between <b><a href="British_English" title="British English">British English</a></b> and <b><a href="American_English" title="American English">American English</a></b>, which, <i>for the purposes of these articles</i>, are defined as follows:</p>
